## This guide explains how to install and run **SonarQube** on an AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance using Docker.

Launch EC2 Instance
Instance type: t2.medium (at least 2 vCPU + 4GB RAM)
Storage: 20GB recommende
Security Group:
              Allow ports:9000 (SonarQube Web UI)

Step 1: Update Packages
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Install Docker (Driver for Minikube)
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER && newgrp docker

Step 3:Pull SonarQube Docker Image
docker pull sonarqube:lts

Step 4:Run SonarQube Container
docker run -d --name sonarqube \
  -p 9000:9000 \
  sonarqube:lts
  
Step 5:Verify Container
docker ps
You should see sonarqube running.

Step 6:Access SonarQube UI
Open a browser: http://<EC2-Public-IP>:9000

Step 7:Verification
curl http://localhost:9000
ðŸ‘‰ If successful, you should get an HTML response.
